Now, allow me to present a simpler proof of the resolution. I'll do my best to explain each step. 1/3 = 0.333... [Any calculator can confirm this] 3*(1/3) = 3*(0.333...) The answer is simple, as the 3's in 0.333... never actually end, the multiplication simply consists of making them all nines, of course if it was a finite number I could not do this proof either. It would fail at the very first step. 1/3 = 0.333 [WRONG!] The same proof works for 1/9, for instance 1/9 = 0.111... 9*(1/9) = 9*(0.111...) 9/9 = 0.999... 1 = 0.999...
